description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthcare Support Worker Band 3 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Team - City Team (Salisbury)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours/ Week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity based in Salisbury City Community Team for a Band 3 Health Care Support.  We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic individual Health Care Support Worker who ideally has previous experience working with patients in a community setting. We have an opportunity to work with the City Community Team working with the Nursing fhhteam with the primary aim of offering support, care and treatment to a wide range of patients predominantly within the home setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will need to have a good general education and an NVQ Level 3 in Health Care is an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full driving licence and access to a vehicle is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are excited at the prospect of working in this challenging yet highly rewarding area of healthcare then we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wiltshire Health and Care are supportive of their staff’s wellbeing and in return we are looking for dynamic and innovative staff, that are expected to work seamlessly across multi-professional community services and to forge close links with other local teams, including Primary care and Salisbury Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wiltshire Health and Care is developing training specific for these roles and will provide you with a supportive, friendly and happy environment in which to learn new skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Elaine Allan on 07747 532716.&lt;/p&gt;
